### Type

@p{@link[../../using-hooks/normal-hooks.html]{Normal}}

### Function Signature

@codeblock[janet]```
(hook-fn top-frame)
```

### Description

Gets triggered when any of a monitor's settings are changed. @code{top-frame} is the top-level frame representing the monitor. The actual monitor settings are stored in @code{top-frame}'s @code{:monitor} property.

The monitor settings include @code{:device}, @code{:dpi}, @code{:flags} \(whether it's the primary monitor or not), @code{:rect}, and @code{:work-area}.
